text: nice newspaper insert talking about Japanese internment camps in World War 2 set on Walnut table. If you don't know much about those moments in American history, please take a gander. WWII (before during and after) anti-Japanese sentiment defined a generation of citizens like my father and by extension like me.
tiny baby mangos on walnut - saw them at Hong Phat and couldn’t resist
They are very cute and delicious :slightly_smiling_face:

attachments.title: People Are Photoshopping Mr. Bean Into Things, And It’s Absolutely Hilarious
attachments.text: Mr. Bean is probably one of the funniest faces of all time. I mean, the character barely talks yet still manages to make us laugh all the time. There are rumors that he may return, but we don't know for sure. Until then, let's enjoy some hilarious pics of him to brighten this dull Monday at work.
